OL,6,FSupporters of have suggested that some
OL,7,Fof the attacks on the First Minister
OL,8,Fhave "crossed a line" into "racially
OL,9,Finfluenced attitudes and judgements."
OL,11,FWelsh Labour's BAME committee have
OL,12,Fsaid that some of the criticism "has
OL,13,Fgone well beyond what one can
OL,14,Freasonably call fair scrutiny."
OL,16,FPolitical opponents have denied any
OL,17,Fracism in their approach to the
OL,18,Fvarious controversies, insisting that
OL,19,Ftheir criticism is only about scrutiny
OL,20,Fof the First Minister's judgement and
OL,21,Factions.
