OL,6,FThere's been no official report of the
OL,7,Fmeeting but one MS insisted that the
OL,8,FFirst Minister received support for
OL,9,Fasking Ms Blythyn to leave the
OL,10,Fgovernment and that the cabinet was
OL,11,Funited behind him.
OL,13,FOver the weekend, Welsh Labour's BAME
OL,14,Fcommittee posted a statement saying
OL,15,Fthat "For so many BAME people in Wales
OL,16,Fthe last few weeks will have been
OL,17,Fdisturbing, unsettling and yet very
OL,18,Ffamiliar. In the Welsh media the
OL,19,Ftreatment of Vaughan Gething has gone
OL,20,Fwell beyond what one can reasonably
OL,21,Fcall fair scrutiny."
