OL,6,FThe statement continues to say that
OL,7,F"There have been many moments of
OL,8,Freflection over the last few years in
OL,9,Fwhich people and institutions have
OL,10,Faccepted how subconscious racial
OL,11,Fprejudice can creep into the things
OL,12,Fthey do and say. We believe we are
OL,13,Fseeing this play out before us, and we
OL,14,Fmust act to stop it.
OL,16,F"That is why we are speaking out,
OL,17,Fstanding firmly behind Vaughan
OL,18,FGething, and calling on all in our
OL,19,Fmovement to be allies, not bystanders."
